==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Statics
<hw>Stat"ics</hw> <pr>(-⟦icr⟧ks)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>statique</ets>, Gr. <grk>statikh`</grk> the art of weighing, fr.
<grk>statiko`s</grk>. See <er>Static</er>.]</ety> <def>That branch of
mechanics which treats of the equilibrium of forces, or relates to
bodies as held at rest by the forces acting on them; -- distinguished
from <contr>dynamics</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Social statics</b></col>, <cd>the study of the conditions
which concern the existence and permanence of the social
state.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stating</ent>⟦br⟧
